						<div class="postbody">I updated my post so the patch actually works now.  I forgot to force the modules to play the first track.<br /><br />But I can't finish the job, because Famitracker won't create a .BIN file for songs that use bankswitching.  The code now, using NSF bankswitching unfortunately, according the comments is paging pattern data at $B000-$BFFF.  VRC6 pages $8000-$BFFF all together.  Of course it's always still doable, it just means more changes are needed.<br /><br />I could make one that plays all the non-bankswitched tracks, if that helps.  I would need to know what order to put them in, unless you're wanting to build from the source.</div>

